    <thetext>Description of problem:
The flower documentation states the broker url can be set in the configuration file, but it is not actually making use of this setting.


Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
0.8.3-5


How reproducible:
always

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Change the BROKER_URL setting in /etc/flower/config.py
2. Start the application with &apos;sudo systemctl start flower.service&apos;

Actual results:
Attempts to connect to the default broker.


Expected results:
Attempts to connect to the specified broker.


Additional info:
Upstream bug: https://github.com/mher/flower/issues/507</thetext>
